r</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/03 8:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3127.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   New 1hb from POE question</span><hr size=1> Last night I won 1 of the new 1hb hammers dropping from POE. <br>
<br>
Here are the stats first (obviously the mana is bugged):<br>
<br>
26/28 15ac +20str +15dex +10sta +135HP, +1135Mana, +25MR, +25DR<br>
Procs: Rune II<br>
<br>
I am a 65 warrior with over 260 aa so all my offensive AA are maxed and this leads to my question:<br>
<br>
Normally I use a BF + BoC combo for hate. However, just screwing around in POE last night I put this into my main hand (I know its slow) and I was easily outaggroing other tanks all night and keeping steady aggro (even with 6 other warriors there). Sure the trash would ping pong off me but once the procing started the mob would stay like glue on me. I put the BF in offhand.<br>
<br>
My question is, how much taunt is Rune II? I sure seemed to be generating a great deal of hate with the weapon. I am thinking it might be a nice way to duel wield with less swings for potential ripostes.<br>
<br>
BTW, it looks like a big ugly mallet so you have been warned LOL.<br>
<br>
Slee <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=coray>Coray</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 177<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/03 10:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3127.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New 1hb from POE question</span><hr size=1> Curious what that came from, heard about some poe changes, but as far as rune aggro goes, it's relative to the amount of protection the rune provides.<br>
<br>
Rune 2 for example is 118 damage absorped, which is probably about how much hate it generates from that.<br>
<br>
Given the dps and proc it's probably fine to hold aggro with. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thorbadintriton>Thorbadin Triton</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/03 1:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3127.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   .</span><hr size=1> Cool weapon I guess.  It's a good off-hand with a decent aggro proc (better then straight dd for sure).  It's probably shitty dps in main-hand as expected with a slow dly like this.<br>
<br>
I've used a rune II weapon a bit (the 18 dly thing from pwater) and even thought I'm certain it didn't hurt, I'm certain it's still an order of magnitude below enraging blow, etc.  It's expected but still make it a somewhat low taunt imo.  Again, low taunt proc is probably better then no taunt at all in most case.  For example, you can &quot;steal&quot; aggro without taunt if you proc a bloodfrenzy too much but the chances of doing the same using rune are very low.  At least it seemed to me.<br>
<br>
Thorbadin<br>
Triton<br>
<br>
