<br>
It give option I guess.<br>
<br>
The problem, and a bit of the reason why I said it sucked was because in the sheet I use the 26/28 turned out very low on the list.  That's mainly because all the high end 2-handers own the 1-hander.   So looking fast it gave the impression that the weapon sucked kinda (it does in regards to 2-handers) but it hold it's own correctly against other 1-handers.<br>
<br>
Still, best place to have that weapon is off-hand with one of the 17/19 or so in primary hand.<br>
<br>
Thorbadin<br>
Triton <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zebedi>Zebedi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.earthlink.net/~zebedi/images/smallz.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/11/03 9:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3127.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~zebedi/images/Zebface1.jpeg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hey</span><hr size=1> I think the reason most of us still prefer a fast mainhand is pure consistancy.<br>
<br>
With two weapons of near equal ratio, you will <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>average</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> nearly the same dps. <br>
<br>
With the faster weapon, your dps vary less, and you will be exposed to more ripostes.<br>
<br>
With the slower weapon, your dps will spike high and spike low. This can lead to loss of aggro.. and bad things happen when you lose aggro <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
That said, there's evidence that different weapons can be assigned different proc rates. If the proc rate is jacked up on the slower weapon (ie<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> roccing twice as much as your EB weapon on average) it may be a better choice.<br>
<br>
Definately a sweet offhand at the very least.<br>
